WEBVTT

00:00.610 --> 00:15.565
Before we get into this story here in John 4 and the conversation that you just heard Jesus with the Samaritan woman, I just wanted you to see something unusual and beautiful here about Jesus.

00:18.248 --> 00:28.818
In the last chapter, chapter three, Jesus is ministering to a curious Pharisee, a teacher of the law, a ruler of the Jews, so he calls him.

00:29.986 --> 00:30.707
Untouchable.

00:34.651 --> 00:40.618
This is a guy from the highest, most intellectual, most religious stratosphere of society.

00:43.121 --> 00:53.392
And yet Jesus reaches out to him to invite him in to answer his questions to challenge his thinking and to draw him into the kingdom.

00:55.574 --> 00:58.898
And then here, just a few verses later,

00:59.618 --> 01:12.230
He's stopping to minister to a sexually promiscuous, socially alienated Samaritan woman.

01:12.250 --> 01:12.831
Untouchable.

01:14.953 --> 01:24.962
And yet Jesus reaches out to her, engages her questions, and invites her to drink from his fountain of living water.

01:26.023 --> 01:29.106
These two people couldn't be more different.

01:31.074 --> 01:37.224
He's a Jew, a leader in society, steeped in scripture, rigorously observing the law.

01:37.565 --> 01:40.450
He's a man and he comes at night.

01:42.533 --> 01:44.837
And we know his name, Nicodemus.

01:46.600 --> 01:56.296
She is a Samaritan and an outcast even in Samaria, in and out of relationships with men, far less familiar with God's law.

01:56.356 --> 01:57.298
She's a woman.

01:59.074 --> 02:02.718
And they meet in broad, scorching daylight.

02:04.840 --> 02:05.921
And we don't even get her name.

02:08.484 --> 02:14.990
These two people couldn't be more different, and I believe that's utterly intentional.

02:16.952 --> 02:17.974
So what do I take from it?

02:19.916 --> 02:20.776
What do you take from it?

02:25.001 --> 02:26.162
Here's what I take from it.

02:26.882 --> 02:30.145
It doesn't matter who you are this morning.

02:31.447 --> 02:32.347
It doesn't matter.

02:33.729 --> 02:36.912
Jesus has something to say to you.

02:40.135 --> 02:54.930
It doesn't matter if you're a politician or a prostitute, a priest or a thief, a CEO or a stay-at-home mom or a college student, a Jew,

02:55.874 --> 02:59.958
or a Samaritan, or a lifelong Minnesotan.

03:02.221 --> 03:18.299
Jesus has something to say to you this morning, something convicting and renewing, something hard and something really, really, really good.

03:20.221 --> 03:21.522
It was true with Nicodemus,

03:21.890 --> 03:27.980
And it's true here with this woman, and it'll be true in this room this morning if we have ears to hear them.

03:28.801 --> 03:30.884
So let's pray and ask for that.

03:34.770 --> 03:38.857
Come, everyone who thirsts, come to the waters.

03:39.778 --> 03:43.043
And he who has no money come by and eat.

03:43.604 --> 03:46.789
Come by wine and milk without money and without price.

03:46.929 --> 03:49.874
Why do you spend your money

03:50.082 --> 03:57.093
for that which is not bread and your labor for that which does not satisfy.

03:58.415 --> 04:13.659
Listen diligently to me and eat what is good and delight yourselves in rich food, incline your ear and come to me here that your soul may live.

04:16.143 --> 04:18.386
Father, you've spread a banquet out before us,

04:19.586 --> 04:25.332
You're inviting us here in these verses to a fountain of living water.

04:26.954 --> 04:31.239
Forgive us for spending our money on food that does not satisfy.

04:31.299 --> 04:36.504
Forgive us for pursuing fountains, wells which do not satisfy.

04:36.565 --> 04:41.009
Give us ears to hear you this morning.

04:41.049 --> 04:45.234
Give us eyes to see you, to want you.

04:46.050 --> 04:51.657
to feast on you, to drink from you, and never be thirsty again.

04:52.939 --> 04:55.482
And pray this in Jesus' name.

04:55.502 --> 04:55.762
Amen.

04:57.204 --> 05:10.842
Okay, so we read here, verses one through three, that Jesus leaves Judea because of pressure from the Pharisees, the rulers there, they were getting jealous and angry, and he's feeling the pressure, and so he heads for Galilee.

05:12.524 --> 05:14.386
And you had to go through Samaria,

05:14.818 --> 05:16.059
to get to Galilee.

05:17.701 --> 05:22.587
But Samaria was a bad word in Jerusalem for Jews.

05:23.328 --> 05:28.854
Jews hated Samaritans, and Samaritans hated Jews.

05:30.175 --> 05:38.845
But he had to pass through Samaria to get to Galilee, and as he did, he gets tired from all of that walking, and so he finds a well where he can stop and get a drink.

05:40.267 --> 05:42.930
Text tells us about the six hours, so it's noon.

05:44.802 --> 05:49.870
The hottest part of the day, no one draws water in Samaria at noon.

05:50.772 --> 05:54.338
They come either earlier in the day or later when it's cooler.

05:55.880 --> 05:57.182
No one comes at this time.

05:58.444 --> 06:02.451
And yet while he's there, a woman stops at the well.

06:04.494 --> 06:07.479
A woman of Samaria, that's what she's called.

06:08.641 --> 06:11.826
So this is Mrs. Badward to Jews.

06:13.058 --> 06:18.263
And as we'll find out in a minute, she's here at the well in the hottest part of the day for a reason.

06:19.865 --> 06:27.352
She's likely ashamed to be around the other women because of all the men that she's been with.

06:29.895 --> 06:34.199
Despite all that, Jesus says to her, verse 7, give me a drink.

06:37.262 --> 06:41.426
You can tell how surprising it was for him to even talk to her, if you can believe that.

06:41.890 --> 06:43.152
because of how she responds.

06:43.172 --> 06:45.014
A simple request, can I have a drink?

06:45.816 --> 06:52.565
She says, how is it that you, a Jew, ask for a drink for me, a woman of Samaria?

06:53.406 --> 06:57.933
For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.

06:59.275 --> 07:00.016
No dealings.

07:00.897 --> 07:03.581
Not even a cup of water on a hot day.

07:04.723 --> 07:05.363
No dealings.

07:06.986 --> 07:09.970
So why did Jews and Samaritans hate one another so much?

07:11.202 --> 07:17.851
Well, in the beginning, the nation of Israel had 12 tribes, one each for the 12 sons of Jacob.

07:18.432 --> 07:22.437
And the capital of that nation was and is still today, Jerusalem.

07:23.319 --> 07:27.885
And Israel still had those 12 tribes when Solomon was king.

07:27.965 --> 07:29.848
Solomon was David's son.

07:31.370 --> 07:40.242
But when Solomon died and his son, Rehoboam, took over, he ruled badly and he alienated 10 of the 12 tribes

07:40.866 --> 07:41.687
of Israel.

07:42.849 --> 07:48.996
So those 10 tribes, they formed a northern kingdom, a separate kingdom, and they made Jeroboam their king.

07:50.258 --> 07:52.721
And that made them traitors in Jerusalem.

07:54.643 --> 07:59.409
And Samaria was the capital of that traitor nation.

08:01.392 --> 08:09.362
Foreigners moved into Samaria after that, and they intermarried with the Jewish people, making them the people there less and less Jewish over time.

08:09.538 --> 08:20.872
And so for the Jews, Samaritan was anonymous with half-breed, impure, not really Jewish.

08:22.434 --> 08:24.577
They despised Samaritans.

08:25.438 --> 08:34.770
One scholar writes, the ethnic and cultural boundary between the Jews and the Samaritans was every bit as rigid and hostile

08:34.850 --> 08:41.757
as the current boundary between blacks and whites in the most racist areas of the United States.

08:44.940 --> 08:50.565
Imagine being refused a cup of water because of your ethnicity.

08:53.868 --> 08:56.791
That's how malicious this rivalry was.

08:58.413 --> 08:59.834
But Jesus, he's not offended.

08:59.894 --> 09:04.178
He answers verse 10, if you knew the gift of God,

09:04.738 --> 09:14.152
And who it is that is saying to you, give me a drink, you would have asked him and he would have given you living water.

09:16.155 --> 09:23.647
You think you've got me figured out that I'm like every other Jewish guy that you've heard about, but you have no idea who I am.

09:23.827 --> 09:30.898
If you knew who I was, you wouldn't have waited for me to ask you for a drink.

09:34.018 --> 09:35.220
She's, of course, confused.

09:35.600 --> 09:36.041
Wouldn't you be?

09:37.723 --> 09:44.113
So she says, sir, you have nothing to draw water with and the well is deep.

09:45.295 --> 09:47.438
Where do you get that living water?

09:48.479 --> 09:50.963
Are you greater than our father, Jacob?

09:51.003 --> 09:59.376
He gave us this well and drank from it himself as did his sons and his livestock.

09:59.396 --> 10:03.762
What she's saying, she's saying, the water's been just fine for me.

10:05.122 --> 10:08.485
And for hundreds of years, this well has provided water.

10:08.565 --> 10:17.194
In fact, I just read this week that this well, we think it's this well, Jacob's well, is still producing water even now, today.

10:18.295 --> 10:21.638
So as far as wells go, this is a pretty good one.

10:23.180 --> 10:24.821
Why would I need different water?

10:26.663 --> 10:30.267
And besides, if you had better water, what would you even put it in?

10:31.068 --> 10:32.529
Is what she's saying.

10:32.549 --> 10:33.490
You don't have a bucket.

10:36.834 --> 10:43.342
to which he replies, has this water really been enough for you?

10:46.386 --> 10:52.053
And if it has, why do you keep coming back here over and over and over again?

10:53.335 --> 10:54.176
This is how he says it.

10:54.917 --> 10:58.722
Everyone who drinks of this water will be thirsty again.

10:59.683 --> 11:05.010
But whoever drinks of the water that I will give him will never be thirsty again.

11:06.050 --> 11:13.801
The water that I will give him will become in him a spring of water welling up to eternal life."

11:14.963 --> 11:17.206
So what do we learn about this living water?

11:17.566 --> 11:22.053
When you drink it, you'll never be thirsty again.

11:22.073 --> 11:26.659
It might be hard for us to feel what this would have meant in that day.

11:26.699 --> 11:34.450
We have clean water everywhere that we turn, coming out of every faucet in our homes, depending on what county you're in.

11:36.514 --> 11:45.285
In that day, they had to carry these buckets back and forth, back and forth, back and forth for drinking, for cooking, for bathing.

11:45.546 --> 11:48.369
Water was a huge part of their lives.

11:48.810 --> 11:53.296
Their everyday lives, just acquiring water was a huge part of their lives.

11:53.336 --> 11:58.022
And Jesus says, you drink from my well, and you'll never be thirsty again.

11:58.502 --> 12:01.346
You'll never have to do this walk again.

12:03.208 --> 12:04.530
But he goes even further than that.

12:04.674 --> 12:12.024
the water that I will give him will become in him a spring of water welling up to eternal life," he says.

12:13.165 --> 12:17.851
When you drink this water, you'll never thirst and you'll never die.

12:20.154 --> 12:23.779
You're going to live forever, he says.

12:26.763 --> 12:29.426
The woman still doesn't totally get it, as we'll see.

12:29.698 --> 12:30.919
but she's heard enough to be sold.

12:30.999 --> 12:38.166
So she says, sir, give me this water so that I will not be thirsty or have to come here to draw water.

12:39.527 --> 12:41.950
Give me this eternal water service.

12:41.970 --> 12:44.873
The gallon's just showing up in my house every day.

12:44.933 --> 12:48.016
I don't wanna come out here over and over and over again.

12:48.116 --> 12:49.997
I hate coming out here.

12:51.739 --> 12:55.783
Please give me some of this special water that you're telling me about.

12:57.725 --> 12:58.866
So Jesus says to her,

12:59.554 --> 13:02.897
Go call your husband and come here.

13:05.700 --> 13:06.781
It seems straightforward enough.

13:07.642 --> 13:10.745
If you want what I'm offering, go grab your husband and we'll talk more.

13:12.727 --> 13:14.569
It's not straightforward though, not at all.

13:15.490 --> 13:16.531
And Jesus knows that.

13:18.573 --> 13:20.515
The woman answered him, I have no husband.

13:23.178 --> 13:27.442
It's a little awkward, but not necessarily a problem, not yet.

13:29.218 --> 13:32.862
But again, Jesus knows more than she thinks he does.

13:34.164 --> 13:41.233
Jesus says to her, you are right in saying I have no husband, for you have had five husbands.

13:42.815 --> 13:46.760
And the man you now have is not your husband.

13:47.681 --> 13:50.024
What you've said is true.

13:52.567 --> 13:52.767
Ouch.

13:56.171 --> 13:58.514
Okay, so we're not really talking about water at all.

13:58.914 --> 13:59.275
Are we?

14:02.039 --> 14:06.486
This isn't about Jacob or buckets or H2O.

14:08.830 --> 14:13.177
No, for this woman, this woman's well was men.

14:15.381 --> 14:23.474
She'd been trying to quench her thirst for love, for security, for life in the arms of a man.

14:26.914 --> 14:33.805
So we realized that Jesus asked her for a drink because he knew how thirsty she was.

14:36.590 --> 14:41.558
She was dying of thirst inside and she had tried well after well after well.

14:41.939 --> 14:48.730
Greg and then Ryan and then Jared and then Dave and then Scott and then Tony who knows what their names were.

14:50.993 --> 14:53.778
And she was still so thirsty.

14:55.650 --> 14:59.794
In fact, she was more thirsty now than before she met the first guy.

15:02.336 --> 15:09.103
Sin is the anti-well, the anti-fountain.

15:11.585 --> 15:14.868
And some of you are drinking there every day.

15:18.892 --> 15:25.458
Maybe you're like this woman and you've thrown yourself into relationship after relationship after relationship.

15:26.818 --> 15:33.505
Maybe your wells are online in the dark places of the internet.

15:35.748 --> 15:43.116
Maybe you're fostering some bitterness or anger towards someone.

15:43.136 --> 15:49.623
Maybe it's indulging alcohol or overeating or binge watching.

15:51.945 --> 15:56.370
The first time you put your bucket in, you got enough for a drink.

15:58.018 --> 16:03.163
and then a little less, and a little less, and a little less.

16:05.025 --> 16:13.474
And now you're scraping the dirty bottom of that well for just a thimble, for a drop of water.

16:16.597 --> 16:18.780
And you're so thirsty that you keep trying.

16:21.663 --> 16:24.786
Put your buckets down.

16:30.530 --> 16:34.456
Whatever it is, put it down and walk away.

16:34.817 --> 16:37.040
Don't drink there anymore.

16:39.524 --> 16:45.454
Come to the fountain of life and you will never be thirsty again.

16:45.474 --> 16:48.178
And all you have to do is ask.

16:48.238 --> 16:50.101
Do you see that?

16:50.922 --> 16:58.354
Verse 10, if you knew the gift of God and who it is that is saying to you, give me a drink, you would have asked him

16:59.330 --> 17:01.692
All you have to do is ask.

17:01.712 --> 17:07.158
You would have asked Him and He would have given you living water.

17:09.901 --> 17:10.661
Why would He give it?

17:12.323 --> 17:13.504
It's because she asked.

17:15.326 --> 17:18.449
All you have to do is ask.

17:19.150 --> 17:27.218
Right here in these verses in front of us this morning is a well, it's a spring, and it will never fail yet.

17:29.282 --> 17:32.767
You don't even need your bucket anymore because the well is inside of you.

17:33.228 --> 17:42.342
The water that I will give him will become in him, in you, a spring of water welling up to eternal life.

17:45.207 --> 17:47.090
So which well will you choose?

17:49.173 --> 17:51.096
What's keeping you from asking?

17:52.378 --> 17:57.426
What's standing between you and this fountain of living water?

17:58.434 --> 18:06.065
I want you to see in these verses that Jesus overcomes three great hurdles, three great barriers in this story.

18:06.606 --> 18:12.233
The kinds of barriers that might keep you, keep me from coming to this fountain.

18:13.155 --> 18:15.658
There's three great barriers and you could summarize them like this.

18:16.780 --> 18:22.788
Six husbands, two temples, and one wall.

18:24.250 --> 18:26.834
Six husbands, two temples.

18:27.490 --> 18:28.291
in one wall.

18:28.351 --> 18:33.478
So first six husbands, was five husbands and a boyfriend.

18:34.860 --> 18:35.501
What's the point?

18:37.704 --> 18:47.036
The point of these six men is that six men wasn't too many for Jesus.

18:49.660 --> 18:51.522
It might have gotten her canceled in town.

18:51.582 --> 18:54.226
She had to go draw water by herself in the heat of the day.

18:54.978 --> 19:01.728
But six men didn't disqualify her from this well, the well of living water.

19:01.848 --> 19:07.617
No, these six husbands tell us that no sin is too great.

19:08.698 --> 19:13.085
No sin is too great.

19:13.105 --> 19:17.251
You know that, but I want you to know it.

19:20.216 --> 19:23.260
Some of you know it, but you don't believe it.

19:23.821 --> 19:24.562
You don't.

19:25.314 --> 19:32.006
You think that your particular sins are too great, too bad, too many.

19:32.046 --> 19:34.490
That's what you see.

19:34.510 --> 19:39.579
This woman's in the Bible to tell you that's not true.

19:39.599 --> 19:40.340
It's not true.

19:44.207 --> 19:50.418
We don't find out that she's been with so many men until verse 18, but Jesus already knew in verse one.

19:52.482 --> 19:56.026
He knew and he still stopped to talk to her anyway.

19:57.848 --> 20:00.090
He still offered her a drink.

20:00.851 --> 20:08.299
He offered her the only drink that she'd ever need, the one that would quench and heal all the aching dryness that was inside of her.

20:09.421 --> 20:21.554
He wasn't embarrassed to be seen with her and he wasn't ashamed to take her sins upon himself, bear them and die for her to make her his own.

20:24.034 --> 20:25.837
if she would just ask.

20:28.421 --> 20:31.086
So will you ask?

20:31.106 --> 20:36.655
Will you forsake all of your other wells and drink only from this fountain?

20:36.715 --> 20:40.701
Will you believe, repent, and be forgiven?

20:44.087 --> 20:45.970
Second, two temples.

20:48.290 --> 20:54.699
When Jesus suddenly knows about all of her husbands without her telling anything, she realizes that he's a prophet.

20:55.259 --> 20:57.062
How else would he know all that he knows?

20:57.743 --> 21:02.409
And so she turns the conversation to how and where to worship.

21:02.489 --> 21:06.494
So she says verse 19, sir, I perceive that you are a prophet.

21:08.437 --> 21:15.346
Our fathers worshiped on this mountain, but you say that in Jerusalem is the place where people ought to worship.

21:16.674 --> 21:19.478
She's bringing up this argument between Jews and Samaritans.

21:19.498 --> 21:23.905
When the northern kingdom split off from Judah and Jerusalem, they built their own temple.

21:23.945 --> 21:25.086
They had to have somewhere to worship.

21:26.208 --> 21:27.991
They built the temple on Mount Gerazim.

21:28.652 --> 21:30.474
It's the mountain that she mentions.

21:31.916 --> 21:35.281
But the Jews in Jerusalem, they obviously didn't think that that temple was legit.

21:36.423 --> 21:38.486
And so you can imagine the kind of animosity that creates.

21:38.566 --> 21:43.794
This is where we go to worship, but they don't recognize the place where we go to worship.

21:45.602 --> 21:49.707
She realizes this conversation is not really about water or even about her husbands.

21:50.248 --> 21:58.038
This is a conversation about worship and worship happens in her mind in either that temple or that temple.

21:58.538 --> 21:59.600
Those are the two options.

22:01.682 --> 22:05.047
To which Jesus says, woman, believe me.

22:05.788 --> 22:14.098
The hour is coming when neither on this mountain nor in Jerusalem will you worship the Father.

22:14.786 --> 22:16.448
You worship what you do not know.

22:16.468 --> 22:19.992
We worship what we know for salvation is from the Jews.

22:20.812 --> 22:35.748
But the hour is coming and is now here when the true worshipers will worship the Father in spirit and truth, for the Father is seeking such people to worship Him.

22:35.768 --> 22:44.658
So for hundreds and hundreds of years, God's people worshiped in one big temple, a building, 150 feet tall,

22:44.738 --> 22:48.445
and a million and a half square feet, massive building.

22:49.306 --> 22:54.616
It's a big massive dot on Google Maps.

22:54.636 --> 22:56.920
It's big, but it's one dot.

22:58.943 --> 23:01.147
Not anymore, Jesus says.

23:02.269 --> 23:07.058
She offers up these two temples, and Jesus says neither.

23:09.474 --> 23:17.284
Up until now, up until me, Jesus says, you had come to a place, a temple, to offer right worship to God.

23:17.384 --> 23:20.668
Now, you can worship Him anywhere.

23:22.971 --> 23:32.062
You can worship Him at 1524 Summit Avenue in St. Paul, Minnesota, a country that won't even exist for a couple thousand years.

23:36.107 --> 23:38.450
What do these two temples tell us in this story?

23:39.426 --> 23:42.951
They tell us that no place is too far.

23:43.933 --> 23:46.317
No place is too far.

23:46.397 --> 23:52.386
The hour has come when true worshipers worship the Father in spirit and in truth.

23:52.406 --> 24:03.504
True worshipers, they worship in spirit, not just with our hands and our knees and our gifts, but by the work of the Holy Spirit inside of us.

24:03.544 --> 24:05.106
This is what Jesus told us about.

24:05.218 --> 24:15.251
in last chapter, chapter three, when he said to Nicodemus, unless one is born of water and the spirit, he cannot enter the kingdom of God.

24:16.353 --> 24:23.022
Two worshipers worship by the spirit, by a supernatural work that God does inside of us by the spirit.

24:24.284 --> 24:27.027
And true worshipers worship in truth.

24:27.127 --> 24:35.058
That is, they worship according to how God has actually revealed himself in his word, the Bible,

24:36.450 --> 24:42.299
and in the Word made flesh his Son, who we find in the Bible.

24:44.563 --> 24:46.967
These are the essential ingredients for worship.

24:47.067 --> 24:58.305
God's supernatural work in you by the Spirit and God's supernatural revelation in the Bible, most fundamentally in Jesus.

24:59.927 --> 25:01.650
And now in Jesus,

25:02.146 --> 25:12.802
who is the greater temple and now in Jesus, if you worship in spirit and in truth, you can worship God anywhere.

25:12.822 --> 25:16.748
You don't have to come to this building to worship Jesus.

25:17.790 --> 25:21.535
You should absolutely join a local church and attend there faithfully.

25:21.576 --> 25:31.090
I hope you have or you will, but you can worship Jesus in the temple high on the mountain or down by the well in the heat of day.

25:32.034 --> 25:39.765
You can worship in the sanctuary on Sunday morning or alone in your bedroom on your knees.

25:40.946 --> 25:46.875
Because of Jesus, we can meet and worship God in any place.

25:48.216 --> 25:53.844
And one day soon, He will be worshiped in every place.

25:55.086 --> 26:00.914
When His glory covers the earth as the waters cover the sea, no place

26:01.698 --> 26:03.120
is too far.

26:04.141 --> 26:05.202
Third, the wall.

26:06.523 --> 26:22.200
Jesus calmed the raging storm with a word, and here he brought down this mile-high racial, ethnic, religious wall between Jews and Samaritans, and he did it with just a drink of water.

26:23.922 --> 26:28.146
With less than a drink of water, because as far as we know, he doesn't actually get the drink.

26:30.178 --> 26:41.371
This raging hostility between Jews and Samaritans, this hostility, this wall, it tells us that no wall is too high for Jesus.

26:42.532 --> 26:47.157
This Jesus overcomes every conceivable boundary and hostility between us.

26:47.658 --> 26:53.064
So what walls seem too high to you today?

26:55.607 --> 26:58.610
Are they walls in the Middle East or in Asia?

26:59.682 --> 27:07.931
Jesus had to pass through Samaria and he has to pass through Iraq, Tokyo, Hong Kong.

27:07.951 --> 27:14.438
He has to pass through Cameroon in the Philippines and Turkey where our global partners are serving right now.

27:14.658 --> 27:23.228
Those are high, high, high walls and no walls too high.

27:26.071 --> 27:29.074
Why does he have to pass through those hard places?

27:29.282 --> 27:40.639
This gospel, he says, this gospel of the kingdom will be proclaimed throughout the whole world, Matthew 24, 14, as a testimony to all nations, and then the end will come.

27:42.402 --> 27:53.298
One day we're going to sing Revelation 5, 9, worthy are you to take the scroll and to open the seals for you were slain, and by your blood you ransomed past.

27:53.602 --> 27:59.931
You ransomed people for God from every tribe and language and people and nation.

28:03.636 --> 28:07.541
Do you want to reach an unreached people with the gospel?

28:09.904 --> 28:15.572
To help bring down walls around the world so that people dying of thirst might finally hear about Jesus?

28:17.554 --> 28:20.178
You won't find a wall too high.

28:22.562 --> 28:27.811
Jesus can bring down any wall, and He can do it with a cup of water.

28:29.373 --> 28:32.198
How much more might He do through you?

28:36.325 --> 28:49.266
You won't find a wall too high in the Middle East, and you won't find a wall too high in Minneapolis, in your neighborhood, in your family.

28:52.194 --> 28:57.921
These walls are a lot closer, and so they might look and feel a lot higher, a lot thicker.

28:59.583 --> 29:03.548
In the case of family, a lot more sensitive and painful.

29:05.190 --> 29:07.974
How could God ever save him?

29:10.417 --> 29:13.841
How could God ever save her?

29:17.285 --> 29:18.787
There's no sin too great.

29:20.009 --> 29:21.170
There's no place

29:21.858 --> 29:25.164
too far, there's no wall too high.

29:26.807 --> 29:27.629
Do you believe that?

29:29.472 --> 29:30.013
Even for them.

29:32.798 --> 29:37.867
And why is it that no sin is too great, no place is too far, and no wall is too high?

29:37.928 --> 29:45.842
Because verse 23, the Father is seeking people like us to worship Him.

29:46.946 --> 29:51.752
The hour is coming, Jesus says, and is now here when the true worshipers will worship.

29:51.792 --> 29:52.533
It's gonna happen.

29:52.593 --> 30:02.264
The Father in spirit and truth for because the Father is seeking such people to worship Him.

30:02.284 --> 30:05.508
Despite all the barriers, all the walls, it's going to happen.

30:06.729 --> 30:07.110
Why?

30:08.952 --> 30:13.938
Because the God of heaven is out looking for them.

30:15.426 --> 30:18.889
He's meeting them at wells and in temples.

30:20.070 --> 30:28.038
He's finding them at big Christian conferences and in random conversations at the gas station.

30:28.058 --> 30:33.984
He's using parents and neighbors and literally coaches and roommates and coworkers.

30:34.224 --> 30:39.429
He's seeking and seeking, he's seeking worshipers.

30:43.133 --> 30:44.594
Does that sound selfish to you?

30:46.946 --> 30:49.971
The Father is seeking worshipers.

30:52.034 --> 30:55.159
If one of you talked that way, it would be gross, right?

30:56.601 --> 31:01.469
If I said, Pastor Daniel is seeking worshipers who will worship him.

31:03.492 --> 31:05.315
You'd say, he shouldn't be a pastor.

31:07.278 --> 31:08.820
I think he's lost his mind.

31:10.102 --> 31:12.626
We don't like people like this.

31:15.490 --> 31:19.254
So why is it any different for God?

31:19.274 --> 31:24.339
Why can he do everything he does for his own glory?

31:24.439 --> 31:29.704
And he does everything that he does for his own glory.

31:29.724 --> 31:34.249
And why can he command us to do everything we do for his glory?

31:34.269 --> 31:40.976
Whether you eat or drink or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.

31:42.517 --> 31:43.378
Why can he do that?

31:47.522 --> 31:51.567
because he's worthy of all the glory.

31:53.189 --> 32:00.058
More than we could ever give him, more than the sun and moon and stars and mountains could ever say.

32:00.078 --> 32:08.910
And because his glory is the best news in the world for people like us.

32:11.693 --> 32:15.538
Why do I find so much hope and comfort in him seeking

32:15.746 --> 32:16.527
worshippers.

32:16.587 --> 32:25.904
It's because when this God finds a worshipper, He gives us the spring of living water in Him.

32:27.787 --> 32:31.033
Worship is our well of living water.

32:31.173 --> 32:36.522
And if He wasn't seeking, we would never find Him.

32:36.543 --> 32:38.546
That's how blinding sin is.

32:40.450 --> 32:49.444
This God reveals His glory by satisfying the dry and weary souls of the undeserving of the sinful.

32:50.646 --> 32:52.068
That's the kind of God I want.

32:53.391 --> 32:55.434
And that's the only God there is.

32:58.278 --> 33:08.114
And this Father was so relentlessly committed to finding you, knowing you, saving you, that He sent His Son into the world to die for you.

33:09.346 --> 33:15.012
The woman says verse 25, I know that Messiah is coming, he who is called Christ.

33:16.113 --> 33:19.877
When he comes, he will tell us all things.

33:21.378 --> 33:27.124
And Jesus says to her, maybe the clearest, most shocking statement that he makes about himself in all the gospels.

33:27.865 --> 33:32.970
Here's what he says, I who speak to you, I am he.

33:35.753 --> 33:36.754
And in that moment,

33:37.442 --> 33:50.180
She hears what we've known since verse 1, that the normal-looking Jewish man standing by this well at the heat of day, asking her for a drink, he's the Savior of the world.

33:51.802 --> 33:58.431
He's the Son of God, Messiah.

33:58.451 --> 33:59.873
And this brings us to the table.

34:01.415 --> 34:06.322
One of the sneaky, startling things about this passage is hiding, and it's in verse 6.

34:06.498 --> 34:07.540
probably read right over it.

34:09.723 --> 34:17.794
Says, so Jesus wearied as he was from his journey was sitting beside the well.

34:20.138 --> 34:22.000
Jesus was wearied.

34:25.686 --> 34:34.098
It should take our breath away to see the Son of God, the Messiah wearied.

34:36.066 --> 34:40.392
He didn't count equality with God, a thing to be grasped, but he emptied himself.

34:41.594 --> 34:47.382
He got tired like we do, and he needed a drink like we do.

34:47.422 --> 34:52.229
He was willing to be we read for you.

34:52.269 --> 35:01.362
And far more than we read, he humbled himself by becoming obedient to the point of death, death on a cross.

35:02.050 --> 35:08.839
So this long, hot journey from Jerusalem to Galilee, passing through terrible hostility.

35:08.899 --> 35:10.661
It's a picture of this whole gospel.

35:11.943 --> 35:14.165
It's a picture of the whole Bible.

35:15.347 --> 35:30.226
Jesus was wearied for you, betrayed for you, pierced for you, crushed for you so that you might worship Him in spirit and in truth.

35:30.818 --> 35:33.100
and never be thirsty again.

35:34.802 --> 35:35.963
He's still seeking.

35:37.324 --> 35:39.746
So will he find worship in you?

35:41.108 --> 35:52.459
Let me pray.

35:52.479 --> 35:54.040
No sin is too great.

35:55.381 --> 35:57.543
No place is too far.

35:59.465 --> 36:00.306
No wall.

36:00.994 --> 36:01.735
is too high.

36:04.359 --> 36:07.584
I imagine some sins in this room feel pretty great.

36:09.247 --> 36:14.735
Imagine that some here feel pretty far from you.

36:16.418 --> 36:18.281
And imagine some walls seem pretty high.

36:20.865 --> 36:27.074
No sin too great, no place too far, no wall too high, because Father, you are seeking worshipers.

36:27.154 --> 36:29.458
You were seeking them by the well in Samaria.

36:30.466 --> 36:32.029
and you're seeking them here in this room.

36:34.573 --> 36:38.741
And we don't want anyone to leave here thirsty today.

36:41.226 --> 36:46.655
So come and satisfy souls by the hundreds, satisfy souls with yourself for your glory.

36:47.497 --> 36:48.659
We pray this in Jesus' name.

36:49.841 --> 36:50.322
Amen.

